parameters: black_curtain

Cabin Resident: Just hang it around there. I'll get it ready
now.

This area seems to have very few houses. Are you living here
all by yourself?
Cabin Resident: Yeah, that's right.

It must be quite a hassle when you have business in the
village. Isn't it tough living here?
Cabin Resident: Alright, it's ready.
My apologies. I appreciate your kindness.
Oh! This is quite something...!

Cabin Resident: Smells good, doesn't it? It has a peculiar
taste but it brings out the flavor.

Cabin Resident: It's not uncommon around here, and it seems
to be quite useful for many things. As you said, it's a bit
tough, but there are people in the village who will buy it
for a good price.

Cabin Resident: Indeed, it's an inconvenient place, but on
the flip side, there's a certain freedom to it. It's not all
bad.
Is that so. It seems I was worried over nothing.

It's not good to measure things by one's own standards. No
matter where people are, they can be strong and resilient.

Cabin Resident: Ah, those who live in places like this tend
to live surprisingly tough lives.

Cabin Resident: So, you said you had something you wanted to
ask?

Yes, that's right. I feel bad for asking right after getting
information about the cave from you the other day, but I'd
like to hear any stories or even trivial rumors you know
about this land.
Cabin Resident: Let's see...

Cabin Resident: Would something that's been rumored around
here lately be okay?
No problem. Please continue.

Cabin Resident: It started a little while ago, there have
been rumors about people who enter the forest around here
and sometimes just never come back.

Cabin Resident: It's not a place that's easy to get lost in,
so it's a strange story.

Cabin Resident: Well, mostly people are scared that it might
be the work of kidnappers. There are also monsters starting
to appear around here, so that's another possibility. It's
unsettling.
Hmm, that's not a good story at all.

Cabin Resident: Rumors are just rumors, after all. Don't
worry about it too much.

Cabin Resident: As for things that are concerning me at the
moment, that's about it.
I see. Sorry for taking up your time.

If there wasn't anything else, as a knight I couldn't just
ignore such matters...
Uh, ugh...
Suddenly, I can't muster any strength in my body...
Cabin Resident: Phew... it's finally taking effect.
You bastard, what have you done...
Could it be...!
Cabin Resident: It's too late to realize now.

Cabin Resident: But man, knights really are tough. Normally
one would lose the ability to speak after just one bite.
Damn...! You've tricked me...!

Cabin Resident: Hey hey, you can still move? You're
persistent.
Cabin Resident: But maybe you should just give up?
Shut up, scoundrel! I'll cut you down...!

Cabin Resident: Ahh, if you had just slept quietly without
resisting, you could have avoided the pain.
main
Cabin Resident: Making me go through all this trouble.
Ruffian: Boss, who is this?

Cabin Resident: It's that knight from somewhere who came
asking about the cave rumors the other day.

Cabin Resident: I was thinking of stripping her of
everything after she got beaten by the monsters in the cave.
But it seems she managed to crush the monsters all by
herself.

Cabin Resident: Tch! That means we can't use that cave
anymore!!
Ruffian: So, what are we gonna do with her?

Cabin Resident: After we take all the valuables, we'll use
her as usual. She's got strength and looks sturdy. She should
be able to work for a while if we send her over there.
Cabin Resident: And if you look closely...
Cabin Resident: This one's quite a catch.

Cabin Resident: She's going to go through much worse after
this. It won't hurt if we have a little fun with her first.
Ruffian: Hehehe, that's the spirit.
Man in the Cell: Hey! You!!
Man in the Cell: I'll do anything!! Please!!
Man in the Cell: Get me out of here!! I'm begging you!!
Cabin Resident: Shut your damn mouth!!

Cabin Resident: I could strip you down and throw you back
into the monster-infested forest right now, you know!?
Cabin Resident: Be grateful I'm not killing you!!!
Man in the Cell: Eek...!!!
Cabin Resident: Bring him over here, quick!!
Ruffian: Buhahaha...
